Adjust rack to middle position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch pieces.

Dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces; place in a large #pot with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to #pot. Keep covered off heat until ready to mash.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Rub with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}; season generously all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Reserve ¼ tsp @smoky cinnamon paprika spice{1%tablespoon} in a small #microwave-safe bowl{} (you'll use it later); rub chicken all over with remaining Cinnamon Paprika Spice.

Place chicken on one side of a #baking sheet{}. Toss carrots on empty side with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. (For 4 servings, use 2 sheets; roast carrots on top rack and chicken on middle rack.)

Roast on middle rack until chicken is cooked through, ~{18-20%minutes}. Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{} to rest, ~{5%minutes}. Return carrots to oven until browned and tender, ~{3-5%minutes} more.

> Swap in pork tenderloin for chicken; roast 15-18 minutes. For 4 servings, continue roasting carrots 5-7 minutes more.

While chicken roasts, to #bowl{} with reserved Cinnamon Paprika Spice, add @cherry jam{2%unit} and 1 tsp @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}; stir to combine. Microwave until warm, ~{30-60%seconds}. Stir in 1 TBSP @butter{2%tablespoon} until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

Mash drained potatoes with @sour cream{2%tablespoon} and 1 TBSP butter until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season with salt and pepper.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Toss carrots with a pinch of @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste.

Divide chicken, mashed potatoes, and carrots between plates. Drizzle sauce over chicken and serve.